    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.12,
      "end": 22.1,
      "text": "Asap's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 23.26,
      "end": 26.48,
      "text": "The Dolphins, the Whales, and the Sprat.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 27.96,
      "end": 33.54,
      "text": "The Dolphins quarreled with the Whales, and before very long they began fighting with one another.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.36,
      "end": 39.5,
      "text": "The battle was very fierce, and had lasted some time without any sign of coming to an end.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 40.34,
      "end": 42.9,
      "text": "When a Sprat thought that perhaps he could stop it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 43.5,
      "end": 47.2,
      "text": "So he stepped in and tried to persuade them to give up fighting and make friends.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 48.1,
      "end": 50.72,
      "text": "But one of the Dolphins said to him contemptuously,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 51.72,
      "end": 56.8,
      "text": "We would rather go on fighting till we're all killed than be reconciled by a Sprat like you.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 58.34,
      "end": 61.62,
      "text": "End of the Dolphins, the Whales, and the Sprat.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
